sec.p:
As reflected in the described case of F, hypnosis and biofeedback share similar (if not identical) characteristics, including:
positive expectations for therapeutic outcomes;
absorption/concentration/focused, narrowed attention;
spontaneous relaxation in association with vigilant attention;
concurrent psychophysiological changes (used to give feedback to the subject that they are “doing this ‘exactly right’”—biofeedback clinicians may simply refer to these as encouragement or positive verbal feedback).
